Comment_contributor: The origin of taꞌutini is a little more complicated. It was probably borrowed from Tahitian tauatini, whereby the second a disappeared and a glottal was introduced between the first two vowels. Tahitian tauatini itself is a development from the older form tautani, from Eng. ‘thousand’.
